1
00:00:11,583 --> 00:00:12,375
Oh ho.

2
00:00:13,875 --> 00:00:15,416
White-Tee Lychee.

3
00:00:16,875 --> 00:00:18,291
What did you just say?

4
00:00:21,666 --> 00:00:24,250
Aww, all pale and tender.

5
00:00:25,166 --> 00:00:26,875
Just like a lychee.

6
00:00:35,708 --> 00:00:37,083
Beautiful once you peel it.

7
00:00:37,958 --> 00:00:38,916
And the taste—

8
00:00:43,291 --> 00:00:44,125
Mm.

9
00:00:44,875 --> 00:00:47,250
even more juicy.

10
00:00:47,583 --> 00:00:48,916
Don't talk crap.

11
00:00:50,166 --> 00:00:51,416
Hey, get away from me.

12
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:52,416
You reek of liquor.

13
00:00:56,041 --> 00:00:57,833
Cute is cute.

14
00:00:58,291 --> 00:00:59,583
Just a little dim.

15
00:01:01,125 --> 00:01:01,916
Hey.

16
00:01:02,791 --> 00:01:04,125
I meant the lychee.

17
00:01:07,416 --> 00:01:08,541
Keep talking trash—

18
00:01:09,375 --> 00:01:10,666
and I'm filing a complaint.

19
00:01:10,791 --> 00:01:13,291
Hey, threatening me again.

20
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,125
You win.

21
00:01:20,583 --> 00:01:21,416
Hey.

22
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,666
That's my cup.

23
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:27,875
Give it back.

24
00:01:32,250 --> 00:01:33,041
Hey.

25
00:01:37,958 --> 00:01:39,083
Petty.

26
00:01:40,291 --> 00:01:42,208
I just like your cup.

27
00:01:43,916 --> 00:01:45,541
I just figured—

28
00:01:46,125 --> 00:01:47,541
yours was too plain.

29
00:01:48,458 --> 00:01:49,666
Lemme add some,

30
00:01:50,458 --> 00:01:52,666
high-protein stuff.

31
00:01:58,041 --> 00:02:00,541
Da da da da.

32
00:02:01,666 --> 00:02:03,666
Da da da da.

33
00:02:59,791 --> 00:03:01,000
Hey, Senior Zhou.

34
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:01,916
How's it going?

35
00:03:02,208 --> 00:03:03,750
Found yourself a fling in Lijiang yet?

36
00:03:04,291 --> 00:03:05,708
Fling, my ass.

37
00:03:05,708 --> 00:03:08,000
Professor's hounding me for the data like he wants me dead.

38
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:10,708
I'm flying out tomorrow and haven't been anywhere.

39
00:03:10,708 --> 00:03:12,041
Data's not done either.

40
00:03:12,708 --> 00:03:15,000
Damn, that's tragic.

41
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,833
Lijiang for nothing.

42
00:03:16,916 --> 00:03:18,250
I'm not you.

43
00:03:18,375 --> 00:03:19,750
I don't need a fling.

44
00:03:20,083 --> 00:03:21,791
Don't be such a prude.

45
00:03:21,791 --> 00:03:24,750
How old are you, still acting like a scared little quail?

46
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:27,666
Tell you what—send me your data,

47
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:28,666
I'll wrap it up for you.

48
00:03:29,583 --> 00:03:31,708
Now download LIKE on your phone.

49
00:03:32,458 --> 00:03:33,583
Doesn't matter, guy or girl,

50
00:03:33,583 --> 00:03:34,750
just match with someone.

51
00:03:35,416 --> 00:03:37,416
Drinks, dinner, photo trips—

52
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:39,041
go go go.

53
00:03:39,041 --> 00:03:39,958
Uh.

54
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,375
It's fine, I'm okay on my own.

55
00:03:42,416 --> 00:03:44,500
Ugh, stop dragging your feet.

56
00:03:44,708 --> 00:03:46,708
Don't waste this Lijiang trip.

57
00:03:46,958 --> 00:03:48,375
Get out and have a drink. Now.

58
00:04:23,833 --> 00:04:25,583
It's just a drinking buddy.

59
00:04:46,625 --> 00:04:47,458
Hey.

60
00:04:47,958 --> 00:04:48,958
He's right.

61
00:04:48,958 --> 00:04:50,416
Came all the way to Lijiang—

62
00:04:50,416 --> 00:04:53,708
no nightlife, no drinks? What a waste.

63
00:05:42,708 --> 00:05:43,500
Oh ho.

64
00:05:44,041 --> 00:05:46,958
Little Lychee couldn't help himself, huh?

65
00:05:48,041 --> 00:05:48,833
You—

66
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:56,208
White shirt, black shorts, white sneakers.

67
00:05:57,291 --> 00:05:58,666
I mean you.

68
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:00,625
How is it you?

69
00:06:00,625 --> 00:06:01,916
Were you following me?

70
00:06:01,916 --> 00:06:02,625
Hey.

71
00:06:03,375 --> 00:06:04,791
Don't go saying weird things.

72
00:06:04,875 --> 00:06:06,291
You liked me first.

73
00:06:08,625 --> 00:06:09,458
Maybe...

74
00:06:10,708 --> 00:06:12,416
we're just fated.

75
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,458
Fate, my ass.

76
00:06:14,458 --> 00:06:15,666
Creep.

77
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:16,375
Hey.

78
00:06:17,166 --> 00:06:18,291
All right, creep—

79
00:06:19,791 --> 00:06:21,583
can I buy you a drink?

80
00:06:23,791 --> 00:06:24,708
Fine.

81
00:06:25,458 --> 00:06:27,166
Ha, let's get this party going.

82
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:28,833
Excuse me.

83
00:06:33,166 --> 00:06:36,166
This drink—lychee-flavored.

84
00:06:38,083 --> 00:06:40,500
Suits you, perfectly.

85
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:43,500
Can you be serious for a second?

86
00:06:44,458 --> 00:06:47,125
Okay. Since you came tonight,

87
00:06:47,291 --> 00:06:48,583
I'll do whatever you say.

88
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,125
Go on, give it a taste,

89
00:06:53,958 --> 00:06:55,041
Didi.

90
00:06:58,666 --> 00:06:59,458
How is it,

91
00:07:00,041 --> 00:07:01,125
Didi?

92
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:06,083
Why does it sound so weird whenever you call me anything?

93
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:07,000
Does it?

94
00:07:07,250 --> 00:07:09,458
Yeah. Sounds dirty.

95
00:07:09,666 --> 00:07:11,541
Aren't you called Didi?

96
00:07:11,666 --> 00:07:13,291
Or could it be...

97
00:07:13,875 --> 00:07:16,458
you're the one with the dirty mind.

98
00:07:17,791 --> 00:07:19,541
You're the one with the dirty mind.

99
00:07:20,916 --> 00:07:21,791
So,

100
00:07:22,416 --> 00:07:23,666
how's the drink?

101
00:07:24,208 --> 00:07:27,083
The boss made it himself, soaking lychees.

102
00:07:30,458 --> 00:07:31,250
Mm.

103
00:07:31,791 --> 00:07:33,083
It's really good.

104
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:34,500
I like it.

105
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:35,583
This drink—

106
00:07:35,583 --> 00:07:37,291
it tastes a little sweet.

107
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:41,250
But the next thing you know, it'll go straight to your head.

108
00:07:42,458 --> 00:07:43,541
For real?

109
00:07:43,541 --> 00:07:45,208
This stuff can get you drunk?

110
00:07:47,166 --> 00:07:47,958
Whoa.

111
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Impressive. Didn't see that coming.

112
00:07:54,791 --> 00:07:55,583
Excuse me.

113
00:07:56,375 --> 00:07:57,625
Another round.

114
00:07:58,083 --> 00:08:00,416
Guess I underestimated you.

115
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:03,583
Quit it. The drink really is good.

116
00:08:03,583 --> 00:08:05,000
See, what'd I tell you?

117
00:08:05,125 --> 00:08:07,541
You should've come out for a drink ages ago.

118
00:08:07,916 --> 00:08:10,083
You looked so tightly wound every day,

119
00:08:10,416 --> 00:08:12,500
like you had a personal grudge against Lijiang.

120
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:15,125
Your drinks. Enjoy.

121
00:08:15,708 --> 00:08:16,666
Thanks.

122
00:08:19,166 --> 00:08:20,625
I'm here on a research trip.

123
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:22,958
I can't go out before the work's done.

124
00:08:24,666 --> 00:08:26,875
Ah, screw it.

125
00:08:26,958 --> 00:08:28,708
I'm flying back tomorrow anyway.

126
00:08:29,666 --> 00:08:32,000
Tonight, let's just drink up.

127
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:32,791
What?

128
00:08:33,416 --> 00:08:34,875
You leave tomorrow?

129
00:08:36,458 --> 00:08:37,291
Ah.

130
00:08:40,666 --> 00:08:41,458
Okay.

131
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:45,250
Then we have to drink our fill tonight.

132
00:08:59,708 --> 00:09:01,333
Let's play a game.

133
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:04,166
Loser takes a shot.

134
00:09:04,541 --> 00:09:06,708
Sure. Drink till we drop.

135
00:09:07,791 --> 00:09:08,791
Excuse me.

136
00:09:09,625 --> 00:09:10,708
One shot.

137
00:09:22,208 --> 00:09:23,041
You go first.

138
00:09:27,458 --> 00:09:29,500
Four fives.

139
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:30,333
Whoa.

140
00:09:31,291 --> 00:09:32,666
Aggressive.

141
00:09:33,458 --> 00:09:35,375
What? You scared?

142
00:09:35,458 --> 00:09:38,666
Pfft. Nothing scares me.

143
00:09:56,250 --> 00:09:57,500
Damn, you're good.

144
00:09:58,083 --> 00:09:59,666
Of course. Keep going.

145
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:12,625
Four fives.

146
00:10:14,791 --> 00:10:15,791
Again?

147
00:10:15,791 --> 00:10:18,583
That's right, again. What, getting nervous?

148
00:10:20,208 --> 00:10:21,125
Four sixes.

149
00:10:21,958 --> 00:10:23,666
Five fives.

150
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:25,125
Open.

151
00:10:27,791 --> 00:10:29,583
You don't have a single five.

152
00:10:37,083 --> 00:10:38,625
You really can drink, huh?

153
00:10:38,625 --> 00:10:39,458
Of course I can.

154
00:10:39,458 --> 00:10:40,916
Come on, keep going.

155
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:43,416
Since you can drink so much tonight,

156
00:10:43,750 --> 00:10:45,166
don't blame me—

157
00:10:45,375 --> 00:10:48,916
tonight, I'm gonna peel that lychee.

158
00:10:50,166 --> 00:10:51,833
You talk way too much.

159
00:10:51,833 --> 00:10:52,958
Annoying.

160
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:54,583
Hurry up.

161
00:10:55,708 --> 00:10:56,791
Fine.

162
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:03,458
Okay, keep going.

163
00:11:05,166 --> 00:11:07,083
Three sixes.

164
00:11:08,791 --> 00:11:10,208
Why so cautious now?

165
00:11:10,666 --> 00:11:12,958
No way. Hurry up.

166
00:11:14,791 --> 00:11:15,750
Five sixes.

167
00:11:16,875 --> 00:11:17,708
Open.

168
00:11:28,791 --> 00:11:30,500
Looks like your brain

169
00:11:30,666 --> 00:11:33,125
got fried from memorizing too many formulas.

170
00:11:33,166 --> 00:11:34,958
You can't even shake the dice right.

171
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:36,625
I'm not like you arts kids,

172
00:11:36,625 --> 00:11:38,458
with your bored asses and too much free time.

173
00:11:38,708 --> 00:11:40,541
Where would I find time to shake dice?

174
00:11:42,541 --> 00:11:43,583
Come on.

175
00:11:43,583 --> 00:11:44,708
Bring it.

